modular-cpp-framework provides CMake targets:

    find_package(modular-cpp-framework CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE mcf::core)

The package provides the following components:

    mcf::core       - Header-only core framework (EventBus, ServiceLocator, PluginManager, etc.)
    mcf::logger     - Logger module with JSON configuration (if logger feature enabled)
    mcf::networking - TCP networking module (if networking feature enabled)
    mcf::profiling  - Performance profiling module (if profiling feature enabled)
    mcf::realtime   - Fixed timestep realtime module (if realtime feature enabled)

Example usage:

    #include <mcf/core/Application.hpp>
    #include <mcf/modules/logger/LoggerModule.hpp>

    class MyApp : public mcf::Application {
    protected:
        bool onInitialize() override {
            // Initialize your application
            return true;
        }
    };

    int main() {
        MyApp app;
        app.addModule<mcf::LoggerModule>();
        return app.run();
    }

For more information, see the documentation at:
https://github.com/Sylvain-RZ/ModularCppFramework
